description:
&lt;p&gt;We have an excellent opportunity for a qualified and experienced Server Specialist to join our Server team at Hampshire Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust (HHFT). The post is full time permanent contract. Based in Winchester, you will also be required to work at the other HHFT sites at Basingstoke and Andover as required. The Server team supports 700+ Servers of which 90% are virtualized. The Server Specialist role is a key asset in maintaining operational activities of the IT Server environment including critical business systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will be an expert in one or more of the following areas:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;• Microsoft Windows Server operating systems 2019/2016/2012 with 2008/2003 migrations &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;• VMWare Server Virtualization&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• NSX Network Virtualization&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Server management – Builds / Capacity management / Patching &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;• Storage management (Dell Compellent)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;• SQL administration - SQL 2008 to SQL 2017&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;• Backups, Data retention Disaster Recovery and full Systems Recovery &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;• Citrix Xenapp &amp; Netscaler &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;• Exchange 2010 &amp; Exchange online administration&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• System Center Configuration Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Marc Scanlon&lt;br /&gt;Marc.Scanlon@hhft.nhs.uk &lt;br /&gt;01962 825996&lt;/p&gt;
